<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript">JavaScript</a> really is an amazing language, even those who don‚Äôt like it need to learn because the web is <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML">HTML</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets">CSS</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript">JavaScript</a>, that is, it does part of the basics of everything.</p>

<p>But writing JavaScript from scratch can be very laborious and complicated, especially for beginners, which would be JavaScript <a href="http://vanilla-js.com/">Vanilla</a>. Therefore, there are several libraries and frameworks to facilitate and improve your applications.</p>

<p>I separated the 31 best by categories and we will know each one of them:</p>

