<hr />

<h2 id="19-vuejs">19. <a href="https://vuejs.org/">Vue.js</a></h2>
<blockquote>
  <p>Official website: <a href="https://vuejs.org/">https://vuejs.org/</a>
It is an MVVM library that provides two-way data binding, adds additional behavior to HTML (through directives) and reactive components. Using native add-ons, the developer can also rely on routes, AJAX, Flux-style data source management, form validation and more. It provides an extension for Chrome that is very useful for inspecting components built with Vue.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="/assets/img/js/vuejs.png" alt="Vue.js" /></p>

<hr />

<h2 id="20-handlebars">20. <a href="https://handlebarsjs.com/">Handlebars</a></h2>
<blockquote>
  <p>Official website: <a href="https://handlebarsjs.com/">https://handlebarsjs.com/</a>
Handlebars effectively provide the power you need to create semantic templates without frustration. Widely used in <a href="">Node.js</a> to generate dynamic HTML pages.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><img src="/assets/img/js/handlebars.png" alt="Handlebars" /></p>

<hr />

